# Token Management API

<%= toc %>

## Get the current token

Returns limited information regarding the current token being used to access the API.

```bash
curl "https://api.buildkite.com/v2/token"
```

```json
{
  "id": "b63254c0-3271-4a98-8270-7cfbd6c2f14e",
  "scopes": ["read_build"]
}
```

Required scope: none

Success response: `200 OK`

## Revoke the current token

Immediately revokes the current token and sends an email to the owner. Once revoked, the token cannot be used anymore.

```bash
curl -X DELETE "https://api.buildkite.com/v2/token"
```

Required scope: none

Success response: `204 No Content`
